Asking Someone’s Name

Formal

	•	Wer sind Sie? – Who are you? (formal) **
	•	Wie ist Ihr Name? – What is your name? (formal) **

Informal

	•	Wer bist du? – Who are you? (informal)  **
	•	Wie heißt du? – What is your name? (informal, more commonly used)

Age:
 - wie alt bist du?(how old are you)
ans: ich bin 24 jahre alt.( i am 24 years old)


Additional Vocabulary Notes

	•	Wie and Was can both mean “what” in German, but they are used in different contexts.
	•	Wie – Used for questions that ask for descriptions or names (e.g., Wie ist dein Name? – What is your name?)
	•	Was – Used for questions asking for explanations or specific information (e.g., Was machst du? – What are you doing?)


